# Home Energy Manager — Cursor Rules

## Project
Python service controlling Daikin Altherma ASHP + Fox ESS battery + solar.
Owner: Luis Albinati, London. Production system — changes affect real hardware.

## Stack
- Python 3.11+, FastAPI, APScheduler
- Fox ESS cloud API (200 req/day limit — no frequent polling)
- Daikin Onecta cloud API (weather compensation active — use lwt_offset, not room temp)
- Anthropic Claude Haiku as AI assistant (default provider)

## Critical Rules
- NEVER remove safety guards or read-only protections
- OPENCLAW_READ_ONLY=true by default — respect it
- Daikin: always check weather_regulation_active before changing LWT
- Fox ESS: S/N 609H5020541M055, Battery EP11 ~10kWh
- No secrets or credentials in committed code — use env vars from config.py

## Code Style
- Follow existing patterns in src/
- Type hints required
- Keep API endpoints RESTful
- Tests in tests/ when adding new features

## Git
- Conventional commits: feat/fix/refactor/docs/chore
- Never force push main
- I (OverBot) handle git commits after Cursor edits
